# Bastion reviewer policy: changes here require human review.
#
# These paths are the review policy and the engine that enforces it: the reviewer
# registry, the workflow that runs it, and this CODEOWNERS file. Requiring an owner
# review on them means loosening a trigger, weakening a prompt, or switching the
# gate off is a change a human sees. Keep every policy path listed statically;
# CODEOWNERS only takes effect once merged, so it must already cover a path before a
# PR can touch it.
#
# Based on `bastion github codeowners`, with the reviewer registry path added
# (`.bastion.yaml` is the live registry; the generator still emits the legacy
# `/bastion/` location).
/.bastion.yaml @jssblck
/.bastion.yml @jssblck
/bastion/ @jssblck
/.github/workflows/bastion.yml @jssblck
/CODEOWNERS @jssblck
/.github/CODEOWNERS @jssblck
